{"decision":"not_done","recommend_promotion":false,"confidence":0.9,"summary":"Not ready for promotion. The shared enrichment-state contract, explicit `@ai-real` promotion rules, and the provided passing `npm run verify` result are in place, but exit criterion 1 is not satisfied in substance because the Mina credential boundary is not enforced as server-only. `src/features/ai/client.ts` reads `LLM_BASE`/`TOKEN`/`MODEL` and builds the bearer-auth request, yet unlike the repo's other server-side boundaries it is not marked `import \"server-only\"`; `src/features/enrichment/service.ts` is likewise not server-only. That leaves credential handling ambiguous by convention instead of enforced boundary, which the task's evaluator notes explicitly say should block promotion.","satisfied_exit_criteria":["Criterion 2: notes and links now share one enrichment-state contract through Prisma fields plus shared enrichment types/helpers.","Criterion 3: the AI promotion contract is explicit in docs and queued task plans, including `@ai-real` and `npm run test:e2e -- --grep @ai-real` when AI env vars are configured.","Criterion 4: the supplied deterministic check shows `npm run verify` passed."],"missing_requirements":["Criterion 1 is not met in substance: the Mina AI integration path is not enforced as server-only, so token/base-url handling remains ambiguous.","Credential handling should be hardened so the AI client boundary cannot be imported into client-side code accidentally."],"human_review_triggers":["`src/features/ai/client.ts` handles secrets but is not protected with `server-only`, unlike the repository's other server-side boundaries.","`src/features/enrichment/service.ts` also lacks `server-only`, extending the same ambiguity around the intended server-only AI path."]}
